    "summary": "As a global citizen my mission is creating social impact and value developing coherent gender and social inclusion strategies in green and climate-smart development, policies and action plans based on practical examples and GESI data analytics: creating a road beyond compliance. This can only be done effectively in close dialogue with stakeholders, in PPP\u2019s. I use intercultural communication skills and provide inspiration, guidance and support at policy level, with investors, management and country teams, tackling complex social issues such as human and indigenous peoples rights promoting child labor free development and gender equality. I work with UN agencies and Climate Funds (GCF) that work on climate mitigation and adaptation in renewable energy sector, green finance, climate smart technologies, agriculture and water management. Social innovation is needed as much as climate smart technologies. As a \u2018resource investigator\u2019 I love checking on good practices, listen to people and share knowledge and implement innovative approaches in international cooperation and investment. I combine strategic policy making with on the ground experience. Experienced with IFC Sustainability Framework and OECD Guidelines UNGP, SA 8000 certified and Participatory Gender Audit facilitator ILO Certified. I believe GESI and sustainability impact is a field of continuous learning. My colleagues tell me that I am an inspirator, diplomatic with vision and humor. Countries I worked in Latin-America: Chili, Peru*, Ecuador, Bolivia, Colombia, Ha\u00efti, Mexico* and Panama*, Asia: Nepal*, Japan*; USA*, Itali\u00eb* (*lived in) Africa: Tanzania and Kenya.",
